It's understood a truck travelling on the N1 South lost control and collided with four vehicles travelling in the opposite direction including a minibus. JOHANNESBURG – Limpopo police are investigating a case of culpable homicide following Friday’s deadly accident on the N1 North which left 28 people dead. It's understood a truck travelling on the N1 South lost control and collided with four vehicles travelling in the opposite direction including a minibus. Twenty-eight people were killed including two children while three people survived. The police's Moatshe Ngoepe says, “The South African Police Service in Mookgopong, outside Modimolle are investigating a case of culpable homicide. “At this stage the cause of the accident is not clear but the ongoing police investigation will reveal the details.”